.TH PHASORSTD_MEM 3 "January 2026" "Phasor 3.2.0" "Phasor Standard Library 3.2.0"
.SH NAME
phasorstd_mem \- Phasor memory management functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B using("stdmem");
.PP
.B stdmem(name)
.fi
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
.BR stdmem (name)
Free a named variable from the VM's memory, releasing any resources associated with it.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBname\fR 12
String name of the variable to free
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
Null value
.PP
.B Throws:
Runtime error if the argument is not a string
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Freeing a Variable
.PP
.nf
.RS
using("stdmem");

var large_data = fread("bigfile.txt");

// Process data...

// Release memory when no longer needed
stdmem("large_data");
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Conditional Cleanup
.PP
.nf
.RS
var buffer = allocate_buffer();

if (done) {
    stdmem("buffer");
}
.RE
.fi
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
The argument to
.B stdmem()
must be the variable name as a string literal, not the variable itself
.IP \(bu 2
Freeing a variable that does not exist has no effect
.IP \(bu 2
After calling
.BR stdmem() ,
any further access to the freed variable is undefined behaviour
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR phasorstd_file (3),
.BR Phasor_StdLib (3)
